						<summary>

						<p>Kāmēśvara temple, central shrine, behind the dvārapāla image in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front, right of entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanachakravartti Rājarāja-dēva (III ?) Tulā, ba. 4, Monday</hi></p>						

						<p>The right hand and bottom portions of this inscription are built in.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 2000 <hi rend="italic">aṉṟāḍu-naṟ-kāśu</hi> for one perpetual lamp to be burnt before the God Tirukkāmīśvaram-uḍaiyār, by a <hi rend="italic">brahmādhirājar.</hi> Also refers to the endowment of 49 cows, at seven each for seven <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamps.</p>						

						</summary>
